shrekless-office-adjusted-up-nikita-down-plus-world-series-game-2/ | title = Thursday Final Ratings: Grey’s Anatomy, Big Bang Theory, Shrekless, Office Adjusted Up; Nikita Down; Plus World Series Game 2 | work = TV by the Numbers | publisher = Zap2it | last = Gorman | first = Bill | date = 2010-10-29 | accessdate = 2016-10-21 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20101103021644/http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/10/29/thursday-final-ratings-greys-anatomy-big-bang-theory-shrekless-office-adjusted-up-nikita-down-plus-world-series-game-2/70162 }}</ref>。本集在18至49岁年龄段人群中的[[尼尔森收视率|尼尔森家庭收视比率]]为3.9/11，在[[北美东部时区|东部时区]]晚十点时间段居首<ref name="Ratings1" />。由于剧情涉及暴力，剧集播出时附有[[电视分级制度|观众酌情警示信息]]<ref name="SheKnows" />。《私人诊所》的下一集《下一步》（{{lang|en|''What Happens Next''}}）收视成绩又大幅回落，观众总数约为821万<ref name="RatingsFuture">{{Cite web | last = Yanan | first = Travis | date = 2010-11-12 | accessdate = 2016-10-21 | archivedate = 2016-05-03 | deadurl = yes | url = http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/sdsdskdh279882992z1/thursday-final-ratings-fringe-community-30-rock-outsourced-the-office-adjusted-down-bones-my-dad-says-adjusted-up/ | title = Thursday Final Ratings: Fringe, Community, 30 Rock, Outsourced, The Office Adjusted Down; Bones, $#*! My Dad Says Adjusted Up | work = TV by the Numbers | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160503125635/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2010/11/12/thursday-final-ratings-fringe-community-30-rock-outsourced-the-office-adjusted-down-bones-my-dad-says-adjusted-up/ | publisher = Zap2it }}</ref>。

=== 专业评价 ===
[[File:KaDee_Strickland_in_Brentwood_Magazine_April_2005.jpg|thumb]]的演出获得评论界高度评价]]

影评人对本集大多持正面看法，《[[电视指南_(美国杂志)|电视指南]]》就把《夏洛特·金的遭遇》选入2010年最优秀的25集电视剧<ref name="TVGuide">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/news/2010s-best-episodes-1027153/ |title=2010's Best Episodes: Private Practice's Assault and Good Wife Empowerment |date=2010-12-27 |work=TV Guide |publisher=CBS Interactive |accessdate=2016-10-21 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160915191029/http://www.tvguide.com/news/2010s-best-episodes-1027153/ |archivedate=2016-09-15 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。《[[密歇根日报|密歇根日报]]》（{{lang|en|''The Michigan Daily''}}）的亚历克·斯特恩（{{lang|en|Alec Stern}}）称赞这集是《私人诊所》品质进步的例证<ref name="Michigan">{{cite web|url=https://www.michigandaily.com/arts/04what-happening-scandal15 |title=What is happening on 'Scandal?' |last=Stern |first=Alec |date=2014-04-14 |publisher=University of Michigan |work=The Michigan Daily |accessdate=2016-10-21 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818024039/https://www.michigandaily.com/arts/04what-happening-scandal15 |archivedate=2016-08-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>；布赖恩·福特·沙利文在线上评论网站{{lang|en|[[The_Futon_Critic|The Futon Critic]]}}发文，把本集列入2010年最优秀的50集电视剧<ref name="FutonCritic">{{cite web | title = The 50 Best Episodes of 2010: #30-21 | last = Sullivan | first = Brian Ford | date = 2011-01-05 | publisher = The Futon Critic | accessdate = 2016-10-21 | url = http://www.thefutoncritic.com/reviews/2011/01/05/the-50-best-episodes-of-2010-number-30-21-291410/20110105_bestof2010/ | archive-date = 2012-09-12 | archive-url = https://archive.is/20120912021821/http://www.thefutoncritic.com/reviews/2011/01/05/the-50-best-episodes-of-2010-number-30-21-291410/20110105_bestof2010/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。节目播出后，斯特瑞兰德的表演立刻就赢得普遍赞誉。《电视指南》刊登的评论认为她在本集中的演出完全值得艾美奖肯定，而且弗里德曼首度看到金伤势的场景是如此真实，令观众几乎忘记这只是电视节目<ref name="TVGuide" />。{{lang|en|[[TVLine|TVLine]]}}网站则在文章中称，斯特瑞兰德是2011年艾美奖最大的遗珠之一<ref name="TVLine">{{cite web | title = Emmy Nominations 2011: The 21 Biggest Snubs | work = TVLine | archivedate = 2016-09-10 | url = http://tvline.com/gallery/emmy-nominations-2011-the-21-biggest-snubs/#!21/emmys2011_supdramaactress_kstrickland_600_2110613092327/ | date = 2011-07-14 | publisher = Penske Media Corporation | accessdate = 2016-10-21 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160910032631/http://tvline.com/gallery/emmy-nominations-2011-the-21-biggest-snubs/#!21/emmys2011_supdramaactress_kstrickland_600_2110613092327/}}</ref>。《[[E!新闻|E!新闻]]》的[[克里斯汀·多斯桑托斯|克里斯汀·多斯桑托斯]]（{{lang|en|Kristin dos Santos}}）同样认为斯特瑞兰德理应得到艾美奖提名<ref name="E!News" />，{{lang|en|SpoilerTV}}网站的温斯顿·迈兹（{{lang|en|Winston Mize}}）则在文章中称，斯特瑞兰德本应获得大堆奖项肯定，但却“都被人抢走了”<ref name="SpoilerTV">{{cite web|deadurl=yes |url=http://www.spoilertv.com/2016/07/throwback-thursday-private-practice-did.html |title=Throwback Thursday - Private Practice - Did You Hear What Happened to Charlotte King - 'Please Do not Help Me' |last=Mize |first=Winston |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161003125045/http://www.spoilertv.com/2016/07/throwback-thursday-private-practice-did.html |publisher=SpoilerTV |date=2016-07-07 |accessdate=2016-10-21 |archivedate=2016-10-03 }}</ref>。{{lang|en|TV Fanatic}}网站的史蒂夫·马西（{{lang|en|Steve Marsi}}）对《夏洛特·金的遭遇》观感甚佳，称节目题材的表现难度很大，但其节奏配合斯特瑞兰德的演出依然令观众沉浸其中，难以自拔<ref name="TVFanatic">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvfanatic.com/2010/11/private-practice-review-did-you-hear-what-happened-to-charlotte/ |title=Private Practice Review: 'Did You Hear What Happened to Charlotte King?' |last=Marsi |first=Steve |date=2010-11-05 |publisher=SheKnows Entertainment |archivedate=2016-08-16 |work=TV Fanatic |accessdate=2016-10-21 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816091505/http://www.tvfanatic.com/2010/11/private-practice-review-did-you-hear-what-happened-to-charlotte/ |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

剧中对强奸案发后影响的表现形式同样获得电视评论员的普遍赞誉。温斯顿·迈兹就觉得本集是莱梅斯最优秀的作品之一，而且没有对案件本身过度发挥，刻意强加戏剧冲突或筹码<ref name="SpoilerTV" />。在线新闻和评论网站{{lang|en|[[Blogcritics|Blogcritics]]}}的{{lang|en|JeromeWetzelTV}}专栏在文章中指出，《夏洛特·金的遭遇》既激烈又令人不安，悲壮的同时还非常感人，对于强奸案的描绘精准微妙，处处体现出高度责任感<ref name="BlogCritics">{{cite web|url=http://blogcritics.org/tv-review-private-practice-did-you1/ |last=JeromeWetzelTV |title=TV Review: ''Private Practice''– 'Did You Hear What Happened to Charlotte King?' |publisher=Critical Lens Media, Ltd. |work=Blogcritics |date=2010-11-05 |accessdate=2016-10-21 |deadurl=yes |archivedate=2016-06-23 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160623041402/http://blogcritics.org/tv-review-private-practice-did-you1/ }}</ref>。珍妮弗·阿罗（{{lang|en|Jennifer Arrow}}）在《{{lang|en|E!}}新闻》网站发文，称剧中的强奸桥段是“传媒史上对强奸最为切实的描绘”，还特别指出布兰登本以出演《吸血鬼猎人巴菲》中的喜剧人物为人所知，但却在本集出演罪大恶极的人物，鲜明对比值得称道<ref name="E!">{{cite web|last=Arrow |first=Jennifer |date=2010-11-05 |work=E! News |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/209713/the-morning-after-let-s-talk-about-private-practice |title=The Morning After: Let's Talk About Private Practice |publisher=NBCUniversal Cable |accessdate=2016-10-21 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160915181540/http://www.eonline.com/news/209713/the-morning-after-let-s-talk-about-private-practice |archivedate=2016-09-15 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

部分评论把剧中强奸场景及之后的余波同其他节目的类似情节对比。阿罗举出{{lang|en|[[FX_(电视频道)|FX]]}}频道犯罪题材电视剧《[[混乱之子|混乱之子]]》中的[[杰玛·特勒·莫罗|杰玛·特勒·莫罗]]（{{lang|en|Gemma Teller Morrow}}）和[[CW电视网|CW电视网]]青春剧《[[90210|90210]]》中的[[娜奥米·克拉克|娜奥米·克拉克]]（{{lang|en|Naomi Clark}}）为例，称两人同金一样是“坚强而严肃的女性，通常在所处环境中占有主导地位”，但三人遭强奸后都没有报案，在阿罗看来，这都属于电视上强奸剧情的惯常发展趋势。她还进一步指出，剧中受害人都决定不报案可能源自更为普遍的文化信仰，“女人总是会默不吭声<ref name="E!" />。”史蒂夫·马西认为，剧中实时呈现案情、以大量篇幅关注人物反应的表现风格让人想到《[[法律与秩序：特殊受害者|法律与秩序：特殊受害者]]》<ref name="TVFanatic" />。亚历克·斯特恩表示，珊达·莱梅斯在她主创的三部电视剧里都加入性侵犯的内容，在他看来，金的人物发展无疑比美国广播公司电视剧《[[丑闻_(电视剧)|丑闻]]》中的梅莉·格兰特（{{lang|en|Mellie Grant}}）被强奸前后的剧情发展要优秀得多<ref name="Michigan" />。

=== {{anchor|Accolades and impact}}荣誉和影响 ===
2011年，[[美国电视艺术与科学学院|美国电视艺术与科学学院]]授予本集电视学院荣誉奖，称其是“电视良知”的例证，赞扬剧集“生动呈现性侵罪行”。《私人诊所》此前还曾于2010年因[[私人诊所_(第二季)|第二季]]第13集《无所畏惧》（{{lang|en|''Nothing to Fear''}}）涉足[[协助自杀|医生协助自杀]]题材获得电视学院荣誉奖。<ref name="Conscience1">{{cite press release | title = 'Big C,' 'Private Practice,' More Among Televison [''sic''] Academy Honors Recipients | date = 2011-03-07 | publisher = Academy of Television Arts & Sciences | accessdate = 2016-10-21 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160810071007/http://www.emmys.com/news/news/big-c-private-practice-more-among-televison-academy-honors-recipients | archivedate = 2016-08-10 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.emmys.com/news/news/big-c-private-practice-more-among-televison-academy-honors-recipients}}</ref>《夏洛特·金的遭遇》获第13届[[女性形象网奖|女性形象网奖]]正剧类电视剧集奖<ref name="ImageNetwork">{{cite web|url=http://thewinawards.com/13_WINAwards.html |title=The WIN Awards 13 Winners |publisher=Women's Image Network Awards |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160814145923/http://thewinawards.com/13_WINAwards.html |deadurl=yes |accessdate=2016-10-21 |archivedate=2016-08-14 }}</ref>，还因真实呈现强奸案入围健康哨兵奖主线剧情类黄金时段正剧剧集奖<ref name="HealthAward1">{{cite web|archivedate=2016-08-07 |date=2011-08-26 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160807043426/http://annenberg.usc.edu/News%20and%20Events/News/110826sentinel.aspx |accessdate=2016-10-21 |url=http://annenberg.usc.edu/News%2520and%2520Events/News/110826sentinel.aspx |title=Sentinel for Health Awards Honor Health-Related TV Storylines |work=USC Annenberg School for Communication and Journalism |deadurl=yes }}</ref>，但最终不敌关注[[亚斯伯格症候群|亚斯伯格症候群]]的《[[为人父母|为人父母]]》[[为人父母_(第二季)|第二季]]剧集《品质和困难》（{{lang|en|''Qualities and Difficulties''}}）<ref name="HealthAward2">{{cite web|archivedate=2016-07-08 |url=http://www.hollywoodhealthandsociety.org/sites/default/files/sentinel-for-health-awards/2011%20Sentinel%20Awards%20Coverage_0.pdf |title=2011 Sentinel Awards Coverage |publisher=Hollywood, Health & Society |date=2011-09-28 |accessdate=2016-10-21 |format=[[便携式文档格式|PDF]] |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160708203518/http://www.hollywoodhealthandsociety.org/sites/default/files/sentinel-for-health-awards/2011%20Sentinel%20Awards%20Coverage_0.pdf }}</ref>。本集还同之后的剧集《下一步》和《归途漫漫何处觅》（{{lang|en|''Can't Find My Way Back Home''}}）一起为《私人诊所》获得{{lang|en|PRISM}}奖正剧类最佳心理健康多集剧情电视剧提名<ref name="MentalHealth1">{{cite web|title=2011 PRISM Nominations Press Release News |work=Entertainment Industries Council |format=PDF |deadurl=yes |url=http://www.eiconline.org/wp-content/uploads/2011-PRISM-Nomination-Press-Release-New-3-1.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160708210108/http://www.eiconline.org/wp-content/uploads/2011-PRISM-Nomination-Press-Release-New-3-1.pdf |date=2011-02-10 |accessdate=2016-10-21 |archivedate=2016-07-08 }}</ref>，但最终败给《为人父母》的第一和第二季<ref name="PRISM" />。

美国反强奸、虐待和乱伦国家网络组织授予莱梅斯和斯特瑞兰德{{lang|en|RAINN}}希望奖，表彰两人“在教导公众如何防范性侵犯上的努力<ref name="AwardsAwards" />。”斯特瑞兰德表示，她曾考虑递交本集同之后的剧集《归途漫漫何处觅》和《盲目的爱》（{{lang|en|''Blind Love''}}）参与[[第63届黄金时段艾美奖|第63届黄金时段艾美奖]]竞争<ref name="GoldDerby" />，但最终未获提名<ref name="NoEmmyforYou">{{cite web|title=63rd Primetime Emmy Nominations |last=Finke |url=http://deadline.com/2011/07/63rd-primetime-emmy-nominations-coming-146886/ |first=Nikki |date=2011-07-14 |publisher=Penske Media Corporation |work=Deadline.com |accessdate=2016-10-21 |archivedate=2016-07-01 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701040253/http://deadline.com/2011/07/63rd-primetime-emmy-nominations-coming-146886/ |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。不过，她还是在2011年{{lang|en|PRISM}}奖角逐中获正剧类多集剧情最佳电视剧女演员奖<ref name="PRISM">{{cite web|url=http://www.prismawards.com/winners-nominees/year-2011/winners/ |title=Year 2011 Winners |publisher=PRISM Awards |accessdate=2016-10-21 |archivedate=2016-08-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821011757/http://www.prismawards.com/winners-nominees/year-2011/winners/ }}</ref>。莱梅斯因创作《夏洛特·金的遭遇》获2011年[[有色人种促进协会形象奖|有色人种促进协会形象奖]]正剧类电视剧杰出编剧奖<ref name="NAACP">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/2011-naacp-image-awards-winners-photos-706254 |title=2011 NAACP Image Awards Winners [Photos] |date=2011-03-03 |publisher=IBT Media |work=IBTimes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160814162220/http://www.ibtimes.com/2011-naacp-image-awards-winners-photos-706254 |archivedate=2016-08-14 |accessdate=2016-10-21 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

《夏洛特·金的遭遇》播映后，美国反强奸、虐待和乱伦国家网络组织收到的协助请求比之前高出五倍<ref name="TVFanatic2" />，网站服务器一度崩溃<ref name="HollywoodReporter">{{cite web | archivedate = 2016-06-22 | url = http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/emmys-how-private-practices-kadee-196385 | title = Emmys: How 'Private Practice's' KaDee Strickland Handled Her Rape Scene (Q&A) | last = Hunt | first = Stacey Wilson | date = 2011-06-08 | deadurl = no | publisher = Prometheus Global Media | work = The Hollywood Reporter | accessdate = 2016-10-21 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160622013746/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/emmys-how-private-practices-kadee-196385}}</ref>。斯特瑞兰德参与制作[[公益广告|公益广告]]，旨在提升公众对性虐待和强奸罪行的认识<ref name="TVFanatic2" />，她还称有许多遭遇性侵的幸存者给她发来电子邮件<ref name="E!News" /><ref name="NoReport" />。节目播出后，美国反强奸、虐待和乱伦国家网络组织称斯特瑞兰德是“提倡在侦破强奸案时采用{{lang|en|DNA}}证据的代言人<ref name="RAINNAdvocate">{{cite web | url = https://rainn.org/news-room/Strickland/Safer | title = KaDee Strickland Takes A Stand On The Hill | publisher = RAINN | accessdate = 2016-04-22 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160422145834/https://rainn.org/news-room/Strickland/Safer | archivedate = 2016-04-22}}</ref>。”

